    "reasoning": "First, determine the value of $ k $. The problem states that $ f_1(x) = \sqrt{x^2 + 48} $, and we are to find $ k $ such that $ f_1(x) = \sqrt{x^2 + 6k} $. Equating the constants under the square root gives $ 6k = 48 $, so $ k = 8 $.

Next, analyze the Street Art Show conditions. With $ k = 8 $, condition (ii) requires the distance between any two spectators to be at least $ k - 7 = 1 $ meter. Condition (i) mandates all spectators are at least 10 meters from $ K $. Condition (iii) specifies that each new spectator chooses the closest possible position to $ K $ satisfying (i) and (ii).

For large $ n $, the problem reduces to packing $ n $ points in the plane such that each is at least 1 meter apart and all are at least 10 meters from $ K $. The minimal enclosing radius $ R $ for $ n $ points with pairwise distances $ \geq 1 $ grows proportionally to $ \sqrt{n} $ due to area considerations: the area required is $ \Theta(n) $, so $ R = \Theta(\sqrt{n}) $. Thus, $ KP_n $ scales as $ \sqrt{n} $, matching option (B). Options (A), (C), and (D) are invalid because $ KP_n $ is unbounded (A), and linear/quadratic growth (C, D) is too fast compared to the area-based $ \sqrt{n} $ scaling.",
    "answer": "B"
}
